com.tractrac.model.lib.api.sensor

Interface ISensorData

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ITimeData

    public interface ISensorData
extends ITimeData

    This interface implements sensor data. It has methods to retrieve all the dimensions that are supported at this moment (at it will be extended with new methods when the system supports new types of sensors). All the dimensions have the same time stamp (returned by the @ITimeData.getTimestamp() method).

    If the method for a dimension returns null, means that there is not a value for this dimension at this time (it can arrive in a future message). The library doesn't interpolate values for the dimensions and only returns values that have been retrieved from the physical sensor.

    • Method Detail

      • getHeel

        java.lang.Float getHeel()

        Gets the heel, defined as the tilting rotation of a vessel about its longitudinal/X (front-back or bow-stern) axis.

        It's measured in degrees, and it's positive when the boat is on starboard tack. 0 means that the boat is not heeled

        null means that there is not a measure for this dimension at this time (but a correct value can arrive in a future message)

        Returns:
        the heel

      • getTrim

        java.lang.Float getTrim()

        Gets the trim, defined as the up/down rotation of a vessel about its lateral/Y (side-to-side or port-starboard) axis.

        It is measured in degrees, and it's positive when the bow is up. 0 means that the boat is not trimmed

        null means that there is not a measure for this dimension at this time (but a correct value can arrive in a future message)

        Returns:
        the trim

      • getRideHeightPort

        java.lang.Float getRideHeightPort()

        Gets the perpendicular distance from the bottom of the port-hull to the water surface.

        It is measured in meters. A positive value means that the hull is over the water. Zero means the hull is just touching the water. Negative means that is under the water.

        null means that there is not a measure for this dimension at this time (but a correct value can arrive in a future message)

        Returns:
        the ride height

      • getRideHeightStarboard

        java.lang.Float getRideHeightStarboard()

        Gets the perpendicular distance from the bottom of the starboard-hull to the water surface.

        It is measured in meters. A positive value means that the hull is over the water. Zero means the hull is just touching the water. Negative means that is under the water.

        null means that there is not a measure for this dimension at this time (but a correct value can arrive in a future message)

        Returns:
        the ride height

      • getRaw

        java.lang.String getRaw()

        Gets the sensor data in a raw format. It is just an String with all the dimensions separated by ";"

        Returns:
        all sensor data in a raw format

      • getDimensionAt

        java.lang.String getDimensionAt(int index)

        Gets a dimension by index (it can be used if the consumer app knows the order of the dimensions.

        It returns null if the dimension doesn't has a valid value at this timestamp

        Parameters:
        index - the index of the dimension
        Returns:
        the dimension as an String
